@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "In practice 1";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p>Let's start by adjusting our box size to use the <code>border-box</code> version of the box model. This makes sizing all of our elements much easier.</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-css">
/*
========================================
Grid
========================================
*/

*,
*:before,
*:after {
  -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;
  -moz-box-sizing: border-box;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.container {
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding-left: 30px;
  padding-right: 30px;
  width: 960px;
}
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>Next, apply the <code>container</code> class to <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> elements throughout your pages to center content:</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-html">
<header class="container">...</header>
<footer class="container">...</footer>

<section class="container hero">...</section>
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>For vertical spacing, you can add bottom margins to your headings and paragraphs:</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-css">
/*
========================================
Typography
========================================
*/

h1, h3, h4, h5, p {
  margin-bottom: 22px;
}
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>To style buttons, use <code>btn</code> and <code>btn-alt</code> classes:</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-html">
<a class="btn btn-alt">Click Me</a>
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-css">
/*
========================================
Buttons
========================================
*/

.btn {
  border-radius: 5px;
  display: inline-block;
  margin: 0;
}

.btn-alt {
  border: 1px solid #dfe2e5;
  padding: 10px 30px;
}
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>For the home page hero section, add padding around the section:</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">CSS Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-css">
/*
========================================
Home
========================================
*/

.hero {
  padding: 22px 80px 66px 80px;
}
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>Example full structure with a hero section and button:</p>

    <div class="code-container">
        <div class="code-header">HTML Example</div>
        <div class="code-content">
<pre><code class="language-html">
<section class="hero container">
            <h1>Welcome to the Styles Conference</h1>
            <p>Learn the latest in web design and development!</p>
            <a class="btn btn-alt">Register Now</a>
</section>
</code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("PreviousPage", "Home")" class="btn btn-outline-primary">← Previous</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("NextPage", "Home")" class="btn btn-primary">Next →</a>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 960px;
        padding: 20px;
        background-color: var(--bs-body-bg);
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    h1, h3, h4, h5, p {
        margin-bottom: 22px;
    }

    code {
        font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
        background-color: #eef;
        padding: 2px 5px;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    .code-container {
        margin: 25px 0;
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        border-radius: 5px;
        background-color: #f9f9f9;
        overflow-x: auto;
    }

    .code-header {
        background-color: #e9ecef;
        padding: 10px 15px;
        font-family: monospace;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #333;
    }

    .code-content {
        padding: 15px;
    }

    .btn {
        border-radius: 5px;
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 10px 30px;
        font-weight: 500;
    }

    .btn-alt {
        border: 1px solid #dfe2e5;
        background-color: white;
    }

    .btn-primary {
        background-color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
        color: white;
    }

    .btn-outline-primary {
        color: var(--bs-primary);
        border-color: var(--bs-primary);
        background-color: transparent;
    }

    .navigation-buttons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }
</style>
